Russia and Turkey: An "alliance of outsiders"?
It was a gesture that ended a crisis.
The leaders of Russia and Turkey met on Tuesday to give hands and announce an official end to the eight-month long war of words and economic sanctions.
But when Vladimir Putin receives his Turkish opponent in the gilded hall of the St. Petersburg Palace, I cannot resist the impression that Ankara wants this reconciliation the most.
There was a handshake, yes.
But Putin ’ s smile seemed narrow-lipped, and he hardly radiated warmth, even for his reserved circumstances.
Recep Tayyip Erdogan, on the other hand, repeatedly spoke of his "dear friend" Putin - according to a report five times.
I couldn't count it anymore.
