Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec closer to sales billion
A high demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted the turnover of Carl Zeiss Meditec.
In the first nine months of the fiscal year begun in October, Group sales rose by 6.7 percent to EUR 798.6 million, as the listed company announced on Friday in Jena.
Asia ’ s business grew disproportionately by 17.1 percent.
Earnings before interest and taxes rose from EUR 89.5 million to EUR 110.5 million, according to the interim balance sheet.
The Management Board confirmed that the Jena Medical Technology Group intends to exceed the sales mark of one billion euros in this financial year.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment and equipment for medical practices and clinics.
The company, which belongs to the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3000 people.
